r, singer\n|years_active = 1995\u2013present\n|associated_acts = [[Psy 4 de la Rime]]\n|website = {{URL|www.soprano-lesite.fr}}\n}}\n'''Sa\u00efd M'Roumbaba''' ({{IPA-fr|said \u025bm\u0281umbaba}}; born 14 January 1979 in [[Marseille]]), better known by his [[stage name]] '''Soprano''', is a French singer and rapper.<ref name=\"Gutierrez\">{{cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=artist|id=soprano-p862366/biography|pure_url=yes}}|title=Biography: Soprano|last=Gutierrez|first=Evan C.|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=16 November 2010}}</ref> He is a part of the rap group [[Psy 4 de la Rime]].<ref name=\"Birchmeier\">{{cite web|url={{Allmusic|class=artist|id=psy-4-de-la-rime-p748789/biography|pure_url=yes}}|title=Biography: Psy 4 de la Rime|last=Birchmeier|first=Jason|publisher=AllMusic|accessdate=16 November 2010}}</ref> After leaving the group to make his first solo album he recorded his solo debut ''Puisqu'il Faut Vivre'' which made the [[European Top 100 Albums|''Billboard'' European Top 100]].<ref name=\"Gutierrez\" /> He returned in 2010 with a new solo album called ''La Colombe'', which included collaborations with numerous artists such as [[Indila]] and Amadou & Mariam. He has continued to work with Psy4 de la Rime: their third album, ''Les Cit\u00e9s d'Or'', was released in 2008, and their fourth album ''4eme Dimension'' came out in April 2013.\n\nOn 19 September 2019, Soprano entered at the [[Mus\u00e9e Gr\u00e9vin]]. His wax statue wears a hat signed by De Bornarel, a [[Karl Lagerfeld]] jacket and Aaron Jah Stone jewellery; the outfit is the one he wore at the [[NRJ Music Award|NRJ Music Awards]] 2018 ceremony.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sortiraparis.com/arts-culture/exposition/articles/198632-soprano-entre-au-musee-grevin|title=Soprano entre au Mus\u00e9e Gr\u00e9vin|website=www.sortiraparis.com|language=fr|access-date=2019-10-01}}</ref> \"We kept this outfit, we thought it mixed ''The Voice'', my career, the scene... it summed it up well\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://france3-regions.francetvinfo.fr/provence-alpes-cote-d-azur/bouches-du-rhone/marseille/apres-maitre-gims-kendji-girac-mika-soprano-rentre-au-musee-grevin-1720865.html|title=Apr\u00e8s Ma\u00eetre Gims, Kendji Girac ou Mika, Soprano rentre au mus\u00e9e Gr\u00e9vin|website=France 3 Provence-Alpes-C\u00f4te d'Azur|language=fr|access-date=2019-10-01}}</ref> he told [[France 3]].\n\n==Discography==\n{{See also|Psy 4 de la Rime}}\n===Studio albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"3\"| Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Units\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Certifications<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://snepmusique.com/les-certifications/|title=Les certifications|website=SNEP|language=fr-FR|access-date=2019-12-14}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|FRA]]<br/><ref name=\"FRA\">{{cite web|url=http://lescharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Soprano|title=Discographie Soprano|work=French Charts Portal|publisher=Hung Medien|accessdate=10 September 2017}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Ultratop|BEL<br/>(Wa)]]<br/><ref name=\"WA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/fr/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Soprano|title=Discographie Soprano|work=Belgium (Wallonia) Charts Portal|publisher=Hung Medien|accessdate=10 September 2017}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Swiss Hitparade|SWI]]<br/><ref name=\"SWI\">{{cite web|url=http://hitparade.ch/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Soprano|title=Discographie Soprano|work=Swiss Charts Portal|publisher=Hung Medien|accessdate=10 September 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[:fr:Puisqu'il faut vivre|Puisqu'il faut vivre]]''\n| \n* Released: 17 February 2007\n* Label: [[EMI]], Hostile Records, Street Skillz\n* Format: Digital download, CD\n| 2 || 14 || 26\n|\n|\n* FRA: Gold\n|-\n